<div class="page__content">
    <h2>Welcome !</h2>
    <p>
        This is the Robert2 API installation wizard, version <strong>{{version()}}</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
        It will guide you, in 5 short steps, to set the configuration of your Robert2.
        At the very end of the wizard, you'll be able to use Robert2!<br />
        But first, let's check if the minimal requirements are met on your server.
    </p>
    <div class="install__check">
        Robert2 API is compatible with PHP version <strong>7.3.0</strong> and earlier.
        <div class="install__check-result">
            {% if phpVersionOK %}
            <div class="install__check-success">OK, PHP version: {{phpVersion}}</div>
            {% else %}
            <div class="install__check-error">
                You must install a newer version of PHP in order to use Robert2.<br />
                current version: <strong>{{phpVersion}}</strong>.
            </div>
            {% endif %}
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="install__check">
        There are some PHP extensions that must be installed on the server.
        <div class="install__check-result">
            {% for extension in missingExtensions %}
            <li class="install__check-error">Extension '{{extension}}' is missing</li>
            {% else %}
            <span class="install__check-success">All needed extensions installed!</span>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
    {% if requirementsOK %}
    <p>
        Congratulations, all minimum requirements are met. You can now install Robert2.
    </p>
    <form method="POST" class="form">
        <div class="form__submit">
            <button role="submit">Let's go!</button>
        </div>
    </form>
    {% else %}
    <p>
        Unfortunately, <strong class="install__check-error">you can't install Robert2</strong>
        on this server because the minimum requirements are not met. After having corrected
        the points listed above, come back here and retry!
    </p>
    {% endif %}
</div>
